events.name: DevFest Minia 17
events.description:
Our AGENDA:

We are happy to announce the GDG DevFest Minia 2017.
We expect over 100 developers, testers, designers, managers, IT students and geeks from cities throughout Upper Egypt and other cities around Egypt!

This year DevFest Minia 2017 (the 1st one) will be focusing on Android, Firebase, Cloud, IoT, Machine learning, etc. featuring a solid lineup of local and very experienced speakers.

The event is free and open to everyone. It is driven by and for the open Google Developer Group (GDG) community.

We shall also host a session on Women Techmakers to increase female participation within the community and to motivate more women into technology.

Registeration Link:
https://goo.gl/2Bi8ip

Stay tuned to receive all updates and AGENDA!

venue.name: Jeddah International Exhibition & Convention Center
venue.address_1: Al-Madinah Al-Munawarah Rd, An Nuzhah, Jeddah 23532, Saudi Arabia

events.description:
انضم إلى ألمع العقول في أكبر تحدي: هاكاثون الحج.
كل عام يقوم أكثر من مليوني شخص من شتى أنحاء العالم بالذهاب إلى السعودية لأداء الحج. كيف يمكنك استغلال التكنولوجيا والإبداع لتيسير العملية وتحسين التجربة العامة للحجيج؟

JOIN THE BRIGHTEST MINDS FOR THE BIGGEST CHALLENGE YET: THE HAJJ.
Every year over 2 million people from across the globe journey to Saudi to perform The Hajj. How can you leverage technology and innovation to streamline the process and improve the overall experience for pilgrims?
Well, bring your ideas to the hackathon and increase your chances to get selected by registering by the end of Saturday Jul 14th using "GDGMinia" tag in the registration form where the question is "From where did you hear about us?".

لزيادة فرصتك في القبول في المبادرة
تأكد من اضافة GDG Minia
في خانة كيف عرفت عن الهاكثون؟

Register at https://register.hajjhackathon.sa/ 👈
More info at http://hajjhackathon.sa/en 👈

IMPORTANT*** We are not responsible for organizing this Hackathon, we are just sharing the announcements with you, so if you have any questions regarding it check all the details on the website mentioned above.

Hope to see you all there with all your bright ideas. 🙌👩‍💻👨‍💻🥇

venue.name: مبنى الاتصالات - ITI
venue.address_1: Kornish Al Ibrahimeya, Al Walideyah Al Qebleyah

events.description:
☞ Asyut
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Google Cloud Platform Study Jams & TOT
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Registration required on the official website
https://events.withgoogle.com/study-jams-tot/

➡ Dev Ecosystem Study Jams
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Study Jams are study groups complementary to Google Developers Roadshow MENA events, ran by Dev Ecosystem MENA with content from Google Developers.

The objective of the Study Jams is to increase the technical competence of the members of our community through face-to-face courses.

These trainings give the members of our community a series of skills that can be used for personal and professional development.

Join us in the second edition of Study Jams MENA!

--------------------------------------------------------------
##########################################
--------------------------------------------------------------

➡ Training Of Trainers
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
TOT is important, because any trainer needs two separate sets of skills and knowledge; The topic they are teaching (subject matter expertise); And the know-how of transferring that information to the student (instructional expertise). Instructors need both of these sets of skills, and we train you on both.

The goal of the Training of Trainers (TOT) process is to give new trainers the background knowledge, skills and practical experience to provide communities the training and technical assistance they need.

These trainings ensures that communities have their qualified local trainers, who can conduct these workshops in a scalable & self-sustainable way.

➡You can enroll now with commitment & dedication!

group_profile.title: Founder
group_profile.intro:
Welcome to GDG Minia! 
This group is aimed at increasing education and developer advocacy for Google APIs and tools. We want to share ideas and experiences as well as best practices for developing Google applications.
